  <main>
    <section class="page-content">
      <h2>What Are Solar Panels?</h2>
      <p>Solar panels are devices that convert sunlight into electricity. They consist of photovoltaic cells that use the energy from the sun to produce clean, renewable electricity. These cells are typically made from silicon, a material that has the ability to harness sunlight and turn it into energy.</p>

      <h2>How Solar Panels Work</h2>
      <p>Solar panels function by capturing sunlight using photovoltaic cells. These cells generate an electric current when exposed to light. The energy is then transferred to an inverter, which converts the direct current (DC) into alternating current (AC), which can be used to power homes and businesses.</p>

      <img src="solar-panel.jpg" alt="Solar Panel Array" class="responsive-img">

      <h2>Benefits of Solar Energy</h2>
      <p>Solar energy is one of the most abundant and clean sources of energy. The use of solar panels offers numerous environmental, economic, and societal benefits:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Reduces dependence on fossil fuels</li>
        <li>Decreases greenhouse gas emissions</li>
        <li>Low maintenance and long lifespan</li>
        <li>Can reduce electricity bills over time</li>
        <li>Creates jobs in the green energy sector</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Challenges and Considerations</h2>
      <p>Although solar energy is a powerful solution for sustainable energy, there are some challenges to consider:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>High initial installation costs</li>
        <li>Energy storage for cloudy days and nighttime</li>
        <li>Space requirements for installation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>Despite these challenges, solar energy is rapidly becoming a crucial part of the solution to global energy demands. With technological advancements and falling costs, solar panels will play an increasingly important role in achieving a sustainable energy future.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="page-content">
      <h2>How Solar Panels Contribute to Sustainable Energy</h2>
      <p>Solar panels are a key component in the transition to a sustainable energy system. By converting sunlight into electricity, they provide a renewable, clean source of energy that helps reduce the carbon footprint and fight climate change.</p>

      <h3>Reducing Carbon Emissions</h3>
      <p>Traditional energy sources like coal, oil, and natural gas contribute significantly to carbon emissions. Solar panels, on the other hand, generate electricity without releasing harmful greenhouse gases. By switching to solar, households and businesses can dramatically reduce their carbon footprint.</p>

      <h3>Energy Independence</h3>
      <p>Solar energy allows individuals and nations to become more energy independent. By harnessing the sunâ€™s power, countries can reduce their reliance on imported fossil fuels, which can have fluctuating prices and create geopolitical risks.</p>

      <h3>Promoting Green Jobs</h3>
      <p>The growing solar industry has created millions of jobs worldwide. These range from research and development to manufacturing and installation. Solar energy offers sustainable employment that supports a clean energy economy.</p>

      <h3>Solar Energy & the Future</h3>
      <p>The future of solar energy is bright. As technology advances, solar panels are becoming more efficient and affordable. In the coming years, we can expect to see even greater adoption of solar technology, making it a critical player in the global shift toward sustainable energy.</p>
    </section>
